The food was good. The salsa was kinda bland.

Disappointed with the way we were treated by the staff on Friday night. A friend and I ordered from Fellini's and stepped outside to grab a table. It had rained earlier in the day so the tables on the Fellini's side of the patio were soaking wet. We noticed there were several dry tables 5 steps away under the awning next to La Fonda. We sat down at one. Then a La Fonda server comes outside and tells us very rudely we are not allowed to sit there and we must move.  Considering Fellini's and La Fonda share a parking lot and patio, I do not expect to be kicked out of a table when it is seat yourself.  Because he made us move we were unable to sit outside because all the other chairs and tables were wet. It was not a busy day and there were plenty of open tables to sit other guests on the "La Fonda side". He should have let us eat for the 20 minutes we were there without making us feel completely unwelcome and kicking us out of a perfectly empty table. If management doesn't want customers sitting on their "side" of the patio, they need to build a gate that separates the patio. Considering I live within walking distance of this location and could be a regular, it is very disappointing.

Bad Experience & Bad customer service! I got there 10 mins. before 11pm and they were already shut down and refused to serve me... Never coming back!

I went to this location for a late night bite with a couple friends. While waiting for our food the staff was so kinda; offering us drinks and were so speedy with the to-go orders. Love the music and vibe. The salmon tacos are my absolute favorite!
A little hole in the wall, but really good homemade salsa and fantastic tacos!

This place is too small, understaffed, and the service is very slow as a result. Go to the other La Fonda locations for a much better experience. Overall the food was good, but had to wait 15 minutes just to get our drinks and then when food came out had to wait 15 for utensils (after we went over to ask for them). Had to go ask for checks too as wait staff never came back to check in. Not a good experience!

Horrible. Awful. From the service to the food. Our waiter was inattentive and seemed like he was in a hurry to do nothing. I can honestly say that I’ve never had a worst quesadilla, the cheese was barely melted, the chicken was dry, they just threw raw onions on it. Very disappointing and will never go back again.

Small loose & laid-back place with great chips & salsa. Piaya and bocadilo con chorizo are my favorite entrees. Sangria is refreshing and addictive. Can't go wrong...
These other reviews don’t know what they are talking about. Great food for how much it costs.
Gods food

First of all, totally different menu here! No free chips and salsa either. So we paid for chips an salsa. We were sitting outside and a beetle dropped into our salsa and we asked if we could get another one. Our waiter said no, because we’re outside there is bugs and we would have to pay for another one... what kind of service? Won’t be back to this location. The midtown one has never failed us!

This La Fonda location reopened but their menu is NOT the same as their other locations anymore. The menu has been scaled back by quite a lot, seems crafted towards to-go orders, having even renamed to "La Fonda Taqueria." The rooftop seating area is no more, having been removed during the remodel. Complimentary chips and salsa also killed off at this location. The food they have available is still the same and tasty, but it's an entirely different experience now. Shame.

I've been coming to la Fonda since 2010 at Peachtree Buckhead. They just returned. SUCKS !!! No menu anymore. I'm here now. I ordered chips and salsa, extra now, ordered cheese dip. I asked for some extra salsa MANAGER SAID NO WAY PAY EXTRA FOR EVERYTHING NOW.  I also have a pitcher of margaritas. I was gonna order dinner but no way now. Good luck but you are screwing everyone now. Oh yeah the gentleman said his name is Israel.

Terrible service!!! It was expensive with low quality food. We are never coming back!

The beef was oddly stringy, the queso tasted microwaved, the enchiladas were average at best. The waitress was sweet, even though it was rather hard to understand each other due to our language barrier. Besides being disappointed with the food, I thought the layout of the place was pretty cool - it felt like an upstairs nook, and was very open and airy with lots of windows. It was too cold for them to be opened, but I bet it's nice when it's warmer outside. I don't think I'll ever come back to this location, but I'd recommend you give it a shot; perhaps we just had a one-time mediocre experience.
A great environment to enjoy some Latina foods.  A dish worth getting is called the Paella.  Seafood and rice, you cannot go wrong if this will be your first visit.

The best thing about my lunch at La Fonda Latina was the iced tea. The salsa was OK, the chips were stale and the tilapia tacos with yellow rice and black beans were almost completely tasteless. And the service was terrible. I had to flag someone down for water, a second person for napkins and utensils, a third for menus, a fourth for a tea refill and the check. Not one sever came by without my having to flag them down (I have to take that back, the guy with the chips and salsa came by without a prompt from me).  They must have something good to eat as the place was very busy, but my experience was as bad as it gets. Will not be going back.
(Translated by Google) Paella for two please.  (Original) Paella para dos please.

Amazing food! Had the Reuben Cubano, which was probably one of the most delicious sandwiches i've ever eaten. My boyfriend got something I can't spell, essentially a ribeye marinated and hickory smoked. Also awesome. Service was adequate, and there's a nice open air dining area. Definitely recommend!
